Africa's fastest sprinter Ferdinand Omanyala is under fire for exonerating the government from any blame regarding the delay on his US Visa. Omanyala on Friday said the ongoing blame game should cease, adding the government did its best to sort him out. The athlete said the Ministry of Sports through CS Amina Mohammed were instrumental in his Visa being granted once the issue was raised. "It was through Government intervention by the Ministry of Sports and Athletics Kenya that I got my VISA. In fact, the Ministry of Sports through CS Amina were instrumental in my VISA being granted once the issue was raised." Omanyala failed to make it to the final of the 100m after finishing fifth in the semifinals. He clocked a sluggish 10.14, missing out on the two automatic qualifying slots for the final. The remarks enraged a section of Kenyans on Twitter who gave mixed reactions to his comments. Here are some of the reactions: